title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\InterconnectLocation
name: InterconnectLocation
description:
Represents an Interconnect Attachment (VLAN) Location resource. You can use this resource to find location details about an Interconnect attachment (VLAN). For more information about interconnect attachments, read Creating VLAN Attachments.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.InterconnectLocation

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.address
params.description: [Output Only] The postal address of the Point of Presence, each line in the address is separated by a newline character.

params.name: data.availability_zone
params.description: [Output Only] Availability zone for this InterconnectLocation. Within a metropolitan area (metro), maintenance will not be simultaneously scheduled in more than one availability zone. Example: "zone1" or "zone2".

params.name: data.city
params.description: [Output Only] Metropolitan area designator that indicates which city an interconnect is located. For example: "Chicago, IL", "Amsterdam, Netherlands".

params.name: data.continent
params.description: [Output Only] Continent for this location, which can take one of the following values: - AFRICA - ASIA_PAC - EUROPE - NORTH_AMERICA - SOUTH_AMERICA Check the Continent enum for the list of possible values.

params.name: data.creation_timestamp
params.description: [Output Only] Creation timestamp in RFC3339 text format.

params.name: data.description
params.description: [Output Only] An optional description of the resource.

params.name: data.facility_provider
params.description: [Output Only] The name of the provider for this facility (e.g., EQUINIX).

params.name: data.facility_provider_facility_id
params.description: [Output Only] A provider-assigned Identifier for this facility (e.g., Ashburn-DC1).

params.name: data.id
params.description: [Output Only] The unique identifier for the resource. This identifier is defined by the server.

params.name: data.kind
params.description: [Output Only] Type of the resource. Always compute#interconnectLocation for interconnect locations.

params.name: data.name
params.description: [Output Only] Name of the resource.

params.name: data.peeringdb_facility_id
params.description: [Output Only] The peeringdb identifier for this facility (corresponding with a netfac type in peeringdb).

params.name: data.region_infos
params.description: [Output Only] A list of InterconnectLocation.RegionInfo objects, that describe parameters pertaining to the relation between this InterconnectLocation and various Google Cloud regions.

params.name: data.self_link
params.description: [Output Only] Server-defined URL for the resource.

params.name: data.status
params.description: [Output Only] The status of this InterconnectLocation, which can take one of the following values: - CLOSED: The InterconnectLocation is closed and is unavailable for provisioning new Interconnects. - AVAILABLE: The InterconnectLocation is available for provisioning new Interconnects. Check the Status enum for the list of possible values.

params.name: data.supports_pzs
params.description: [Output Only] Set to true for locations that support physical zone separation. Defaults to false if the field is not present.
